DarkSword — iOS Full-Chain Exploit Research Project
📖 Overview
DarkSword is a full-chain exploit kit targeting Apple iOS devices, first identified and named by the Google Threat Intelligence Group (GTIG) starting in November 2025. This project is dedicated to code research, reproducible analysis, and defensive technique exploration of the DarkSword attack chain.

The entire DarkSword attack chain is implemented purely in JavaScript, starting from a malicious webpage visit and escalating through multiple sandbox layers to achieve kernel-level control. The toolkit has been deployed by multiple threat actors in real-world campaigns targeting Saudi Arabia, Turkey, Malaysia, Ukraine, and other regions.

