🎯 Affected Scope
Item	Details
Target OS	iOS / iPadOS 18.4 – 18.7
Most Affected Versions	iOS 18.4 – 18.6.2
Patched Versions	iOS 18.7.3 and above, iOS 26.2 and above
Not Compatible	iPhone 17 series & iPad M5 (due to MTE hardware protection)
🔗 Exploit Chain Composition
DarkSword chains together 6 distinct vulnerabilities (including 3 zero-days), organized by attack stage as follows:

Stage	CVE ID	Purpose
RCE (Remote Code Execution)	CVE-2025-31277 / CVE-2025-43529	Execute arbitrary JavaScript within WebContent process
PAC Bypass	CVE-2026-20700	Bypass Apple's Pointer Authentication hardware protection
Sandbox Escape #1	CVE-2025-14174	Escape from WebContent to GPU process
Sandbox Escape #2	CVE-2025-43510	Escape from GPU to mediaplaybackd process
Privilege Escalation	CVE-2025-43520	Achieve kernel read/write and full device compromise
The complete attack path is: Webpage Visit → WebContent RCE → PAC Bypass → GPU Sandbox Escape → mediaplaybackd Escape → Kernel Privilege Escalation.

